    ['Garden of Antiquity'] = {
        id = 800,
        start_npc = 'Al\'Taieu',
        start_zone = 'Crystalline Field',
        start_pos = 'H-11',
        description = 'The celestial capital of Al\'Taieu truly exists.  Though vastly altered during the ten thousand-year span of their seclusion, the ancients remain alive in the city.  Nag\'molada heads for the palace, while you and your companions follow in his wake...',
        reward = 'Tavnazian Ring',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Seeker of the Light',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'The Warrior\'s Path'},
        next = {'A Fate Decided'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = ':It appears Nag\'molada has taken the light from you. Have you checked your key items?\n1. Examine the Crystalline Field at (H-11) in Al\'Taieu for a brief cutscene.\n   - Note that the Auroral Updraft at (H-12) (looks like a red pillar of light) will take you back to the Sealion\'s Den. Sueleen in the Sealion\'s Den will send you back to Al\'Taieu.\n2. Examine the 3 Rubious Crystals to spawn trios of Ru\'aern NMs. Once they are defeated examine it again for a brief cutscene (a total of three cutscenes, one for each NM trio).\n   - You can use the Auroroal Updraft at E-8 and L-8 to place you back at the Auroral Updraft at H-12 to shorten your running distance when doing this mission.\n   - Beware that Auroral Updraft teleports count as a zone and will erase buffs that don\'t persist through zoning and dismiss all trusts.\n   - If other players are around and spawning the NMs, you may have to wait a while before being able to use the interaction point. The interaction points will say "There is nothing of interest here." If this is the case. It can take up to two minutes for it to be interactable again.\n3. Return to and examine the Crystalline Field to enter the Grand Palace of Hu\'Xzoi.\n4. Inside, examine the Gate of the Gods for a cutscene and your reward.\n5. Then touch the east "Particle Gate" at (H-8) for another cutscene and to complete this mission.\n   - Make sure to get the Home Point nearby for future Missions.',
