    ['The Call of the Wyrmking'] = {
        id = 258,
        start_npc = 'Airship Dock',
        start_zone = 'Port Bastok',
        start_pos = 'F-7',
        description = 'Not moments after arriving in Bastok, Prishe begins her search for the father of airships, Cid.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Ancient Vows'},
        next = {'A Vessel Without a Captain'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. After the Mammett fight you will appear in South Gustaberg near the Lighthouse.\n2. Make your way to the Airship dock in Port Bastok. Approach the Departures Entrance (F-7) for a cutscene.  Home Point #3 is the closest.\n   - Note this is OUTSIDE of the building, not inside. You do NOT need to pay for a pass. It can take some experimenting to find the right spot, because you can run past it.\n   - [Optional] ...inside the building, Klaus has some extra dialogue at this time. ("...reports of airships colliding with large, unidentified objects in the sky" "these incidents have been isolated")\n   - [Optional] providing a hint and a reminder on where to go, Carey mentions the Metalworks and Cid by name.\n3. Go to the second floor of the Metalworks and talk to Cid (H-8) for a cutscene.',
